What you need to know:

Rupia opened the scoring in the 30th minute before Burundian striker Bienvenue Shaka added the second five minutes later to give Ingwe a much-deserved leadAFC Leopards coach Anthony Kimani said the win puts his players in the right state of mind ahead of the Mashemeji Derby against arch rivals Gor Mahia next weekendHis opposite number Sammy "Pamzo" Omollo said defensive lapses made them lose the game in the first half